name: SUSHI
dis: Japan’s national dish, sushi, is a dish that uses vinegared rice.

name: NIGIRIZUSHI SUSHI
dis: nigirizushi is a hand-pressed varson of sushi

name: FUGU
dis: Fugu is pufferfish. Despite its lethal toxins, it’s a common item eaten regularly in Japan— most notably as sashimi.

name: TONKATSU
dis: Tonkatsu is deep-fried Japanese pork cutlets.

name: KARAAGE
dis: Karaage is Japanese fried chicken, typically made with boneless chicken thighs.

name: YAKITORI
dis: Yakitori is grilled chicken that’s served on skewers.

name: YAKINIKU
dis: Yakiniku translates to “grilled meat,” and is the Japanese version of barbecuing meat and vegetables.

name: GYOZA
dis: Gyoza is a pan-fried dumpling filled with ground meat and vegetables, and eaten with a simple dipping sauce.

name: KOBE BEEF
dis: Kobe beef is a delicacy, and usually pretty pricey due to its high quality and strict standards.

name: ODEN
dis: Oden is a type of Japanese food that content one bowl of fish meat vegetables stew

name: MISO SOUP
dis: Miso soup is a staple in Japanese meals, often served alongside a bowl of rice.

name: ONIGIRI
dis: Onigiri is a Japanese rice ball that comes in a variety of shapes, designs, and tastes.

name: JAPANESE CURRY RICE
dis: Japanese Curry has the consistency of gravy and is typically milder and sweeter compared to Indian curry.

name: DONBURI
dis: Donburi is a Japanese rice bowl dish that consists of meat, fish, or vegetables served over rice.

name: GYUDON
dis: Gyudon is a Japanese beef and rice bowl with thinly sliced pieces of beef and onion served over hot, steamed rice.

name: KAISENDON
dis: Kaisendon is a seafood rice bowl that includes raw seafood (sashimi) over steamed rice.

name: OYAKODON
dis: Oyakodon is a rice bowl dish that includes chicken, egg, and scallions simmered together with a broth and served over rice.

name: SOBA
dis: Soba is a thin buckwheat noodle that is eaten either chilled (zaru soba) with a dipping sauce or hot in a broth.

name: UDON
dis: Udon is thick, Japanese noodles made from wheat flour that can be enjoyed both chilled with a dipping sauce or hot in a soup like soba.

name: RAMEN
dis: Ramen is a noodle soup that has many variations across the country.

name: YAKISOBA
dis: Yakisoba is Japanese stir fry noodles that include a combination of proteins and vegetables as well as a sweet sauce.

name: MELON PAN
dis: Melon Pan is a sweet bread that has a crisp, cookie-like crust at the top with a grid design.

name: MOCHI
dis: Mochi is Japanese rice cakes made from a glutinous rice that’s pounded into a paste and molded.

name: DANGO
dis: Dango is sweet rice balls that are typically served skewered and found at street stalls or festivals.

name: DAIFUKU
dis: Daifuku is a small, filled mochi.The confection is typically stuffed with red bean paste (anko) and comes in either white, light green, or pale pink.

name: NATTO
dis: Natto is fermented soybeans that’s served with soy sauce and mustard, and eaten with rice.

name: OSECHI
dis: Osechi is a variety of traditional dishes eaten during the New Year.They’re often sold in special bento boxes and the ingredients tend to be very colorful.

name: MATCHA
dis: Matcha is a powder ground from green tea leaves.

name: Baozi
dis: One of China's favorite breakfast foods and an everyday snack.

name: Black Tea
dis: Black tea is a large and diverse category, and what differentiates it from other tea varieties is heavy oxidation.

name: Cellophane Noodles
dis: these thin noodles are made from water and starch extracted from mung beans, yams, cassava, or potato.

name: Tofu
dis: Tofu is a unique vegan product, similar to cheese in texture, and made out of coagulated soy milk.

name: Jiaozi
dis: These Chinese dumplings known as jiaozi, consisting of a thinly rolled piece of dough which contains either meat or a vegetable filling,

name: Soy Sauce
dis: Used in China for more than 2,500 years, soy sauce is one of the world's oldest condiments, made by fermenting a combination of salt,

name: Spring Rolls
dis: Spring rolls are traditional Chinese snacks consisting of thin sheets of dough that are filled with various ingredients, then deep-fried in hot oil.

name: Baijiu
dis: Baijiu is a national Chinese drink that is distilled from fermented grains, usually sorghum, wheat, rice, sticky rice, and corn.

name: Shaobing
dis: shaobing is a type of layered flatbread, typically topped with sesame seeds. It is made with multiple layers of dough brushed with sesame paste and resembles a flattened bread roll.

name: Rice Vermicelli
dis: Rice vermicelli are thin noodles made from rice flour and water. They are often used in stir-fries, salads, or soups.

name: Chow mein
dis: Chau mein is one of the most famous fried noodles in China. It  name comes from the Mandarin chǎomiàn and Taishanese chāu-mèing (lit. fried noodles).

name: Green Tea
dis: Green tea is a non-oxidized tea that is characterized by its bright green color and fresh herbaceous notes.

name: Shabu-shabu
dis: Shabu-shabu is a popular Japanese dish consisting of thinly sliced meat and vegetables cooked in water. The dish is an evolved version of the traditional Mongolian nabemono (one-pot) cooking.

name: Manju
dis: Manjū is a steamed Japanese confectionery product shaped into various forms and incorporating different ingredients and flavors.

name: Sichuan Pepper
dis: Despite its name, Sichuan pepper is actually not a pepper, but dried berry of a type of ash shrub that has a unique peppery and lemony aroma.

name: Sweet and Sour Sauce
dis: Sweet and sour sauce is usually associated with the authentic Chinese combination of rice vinegar and sugar.

name: Pào cài
dis: Served as an appetizer, palate freshener, or a side dish, pào cài is a Sichuan-style pickle made with various vegetables

name: Century Egg
dis: Century egg is a Chinese delicacy made by preserving duck, quail, or chicken eggs in a saline solution that consists of salt, clay, and sometimes ash, quicklime, or rice hulls.

name: Kung Pao Chicken
dis: A staple of westernized Chinese cuisine and one of the favorite dishes of foreigners in China, kung pao chicken is a spicy stir-fry dish made with diced chicken, vegetables, peanuts, and Sichuan peppercorns.

name: Kombucha
dis: Kombucha is an effervescent fermented drink usually made with black or green tea.

name: Mapo doufu
dis: Sichuan in origin, mapo doufu consists of tofu cubes settled in a spicy sauce containing minced meat, traditionally beef, and fermented black beans known as douchi.

name: Dan Dan Noodles
dis: Traditional dan dan noodles are a true classic of Chinese cuisine. The star of the dish is a spicy sauce served with the noodles.

name: Peking Duck
dis: The history of Peking duck goes back to China's Yuan Dynasty of the 13th century. Bianyifang, Beijing's oldest restaurant specializing in Peking duck has been in business since the Jiajing reign of the 16th century

name: Har gow
dis: Har gow is a Cantonese dumpling characterized by a delicate, translucent wrapper enveloped around a shrimp filling.

name: Oolong
dis: Oolong is a semi-oxidized tea that can vary depending on the leaf style, level of oxidation, color, and the roasting degree.

name: Orange Chicken
dis: Orange chicken is an American-Chinese dish that was invented as a variation on General Tso's chicken.

name: Shumai
dis: Shumai, literally translated as to cook and sell, is a staple of dim sum cuisine consisting of an open-topped dumpling filled with steamed ground pork, and sometimes finely chopped shrimp or Chinese black mushrooms.

name: Jianbing
dis: jianbing or fried pancake is a thin and savory crêpe-like pancake that is made by spreading batter over a hot, cast-iron slab with a wooden paddle.

name: Egg Tart
dis: One of the most famous Chinese desserts is the classic egg tart, a delicious pastry consisting of a flaky outer shell with a creamy, but firm egg custard in the center.

name: Chinese Mitten Crab
dis: Easily identifiable by the patches of scruffy dark hair on its claws, the succulent, moist, and meaty Shanghai hairy crab is a delicacy that is large as an adult person's palm. Its flesh is firm, yet tender and delicate

name: Lo mein
dis: Another classic of Chinese cuisine, Guangdongese lo mein or laomian (lit. stirred noodles) refers to any kind of dish made with separately boiled wheat and egg noodles

name: General Tso's Chicken
dis: General Tso’s chicken is a Chinese-American sweet and spicy dish consisting of chicken dices that are first deep-fried.

name: Yangzhou Fried Rice
dis: Yangzhou fried rice is a Chinese dish consisting of rice, eggs, and vegetables such as carrots, mushrooms, peas, while the common additions also include shrimps, meat, scallions, and Chinese ham

name: Liangpi
dis: Liangpi is a noodle dish that originated in China's Shaanxi province.this is one of China's popular noodles dish.

name: Twice Cooked Pork
dis: Twice cooked pork is a Sichuan specialty prepared by cooking fatty pork leg or belly (with the skin intact) in two different ways. Pork is first simmered in a pot and cooled in the refrigerator in order for the meat and fat to firm up.

name: Corn & Cauliflower Soup
dis: A gorgeous, thick and creamy soup native to the corn producing countries this will definitely make you winter delicious, comfortable and warm.

name: Chicken & Cheese Salad
dis: It’s as tasty as it can get; a sparkling salad with tender chicken breasts and cheese tossed and mixed in salt, pepper and a generous amount of mayonnaise.

name: Paneer Steak
dis: Let us give an Indian touch to Europe. What’s more Indian than Paneer? I can’t come up with anything!

name: Eggy Bread Blt

name: Grilled Chicken Breasts With Chilies & Lemongrass
dis: Grilled Chicken rustled up with lemongrass and chillies with some red wine sauce to top the dish makes it absolutely stunning.

name: Broccoli Bake
dis: Who likes Broccoli ? One in a hundred may be. Rest assure this dish going to change your perspective on Broccoli

name: Buttered Potatoes

name: Chilly Garlic Wings
dis: The Chicken Wings are richly coated with marinated garlic and chilly. This marinated chicken is then baked and served.

name: Cream Potato Salad
dis: It is nothing but a rich potato salad with loads of mayonnaise and with a little addition of cream.

name: Chicken Roast
dis: The basic roasted chicken which is enchanting, succulent and downright delicious.

name: Chickpea Soup
dis: Warm and comfortable chickpea soup enhanced with leeks, celery, zucchini, squash, bell peppers and white wine flavours for even better taste.

name: Corn & Raw Mango Salad
dis: Corn and mango sounds summer right? What? Yes it is. You got to try this one though.

name: Honey & Whole Grain Mustard Chicken
dis: Chicken marinated in honey and homemade mustard paste, baked till tender.

name: Barbequed Chicken
dis: Well Barbeque is mostly associated with summers but here picnic means winter. What is better than a barbeque in picnic?

name: French Fries
dis: These define Snacks! French fries make snacking, a much better experience.

name: Egg Or Eggless Pancakes
dis: Whether you are a vegetarian or a non-vegetarian; you have to have interest regarding pancakes

dis: Roti is a flat and unleavened bread made with wholemeal flour. It is traditionally cooked on an iron griddle called tava, an important vessel in the Indian cuisine. In Indian cuisine,

name: plane naan
dis: Naan is a unique and popular flatbread with a chewy texture that has its roots in India. The first documented traces of naan are found in the 1300 AD notes of Amir Kushrau.

name: Biryani
dis: Biryani is a group of classic dishes dating back to the Mughal Empire.

name: Dal
dis: This flavorful and highly nutritious national dish of India is especially popular in southern parts of the country,

name: Tandoori
dis: The most popular Indian dishes are those cooked over a blazing fire in the so-called tandoor, a cylindrical open-top clay oven fueled by wood or charcoal.

name: Butter Chicken
dis: Probably the best known of all Indian dishes, butter chicken, also known as murgh makhani, is a staple dish at most Indian restaurants

name: Korma
dis: Korma is a creamy meat stew (although it could also be made in a vegetarian version) with a mild flavor.

name: Tikka
dis: Indian tikka is a dish consisting of boneless meat, usually chicken, that is cut into smaller pieces and marinated in yogurt and traditional Indian spices such as turmeric, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper,

name: Tandoori Chicken
dis: Tandoori chicken or tandoori murgh is one of the most popular dishes in Indian cuisine, its name derived from the Persian word tannur, meaning fire.

name: Paratha
dis: Golden-brown in color, flaky and layered, paratha is a type of Indian bread that is typically consumed for breakfast.

name: Dosa
dis: The thin pancake known as dosa is one of the most famous Indian dishes. It is made with soaked rice and black gram beans,

name: Chapati
dis: Chapati is an unleavened flatbread made with whole wheat flour, water, and salt.

name: Vindaloo
dis: Vindaloo is a flavorful curry dish that is popular in England and the Indian regions of Goa and Konkan.

name: Samosa
dis: Due to their crunchy texture and a variety of different flavors, samosas provide a perfect introduction to the world of Indian cuisine for newcomers.

name: Kheer
dis: Kheer or payasam is an ancient Indian dessert, a creamy rice pudding that is made in several versions across the country.

name: Vada pav
dis: Vada pav is one of Mumbai's favorite sandwiches, its name referring to the key ingredients: vada, or spicy mashed potatoes that are deep-fried in chickpea batter, and pav, or white bread rolls.

name: Khichdi
dis: Khichdi is a South Asian dish consisting of rice and lentils, its name derived from the Sanskrit khiccā, denoting a dish of rice and legumes.

name: Pulao
dis: Pilaf is a staple of Middle Eastern cuisine, a dish made with rice, cracked wheat, couscous, or bulgur.

name: Hyderabadi biryani
dis: Hyderabadi biryani is a South Indian dish consisting of basmati rice, goat, mutton, or chicken meat, lemon, yogurt, onions, and saffron.

name: Upma
dis: Upma is a wholesome Indian dish made with dry semolina or rice flour, cooked into a thick porridge. Traditionally served hot for breakfast.

name: Panipuri
dis: Panipuri is a street snack that is extremely popular in India, Bangladesh, Pakistan, and Nepal.

name: Sambar

name: Palak paneer

name: Dal makhani

name: Keema
dis: Keema is a stew that is usually prepared as a curry with ingredients such as minced lamb or goat meat, green peas, potatoes, ginger, chili, onions, ghee, garlic, and garam masala spices

name: Papadum

name: Ras malai
dis: Ras malai is a popular Indian dessert consisting of white cream, sugar, milk, and cardamom-flavored paneer cheese known as chhana.

name: Gulab jamun

name: Chicken 65

name: Kulfi
dis: Kulfi is a traditional Indian ice cream made with slowly simmered whole milk. Although the long-simmering process results in a loss of volume.

name: Masala dosa
dis: A traditional southern Indian dish known as masala dosa is popular throughout the country.

name: Pav bhaji
dis: Pav bhaji is a popular street snack originating from the Indian state of Maharashtra. It consists of a vegetable curry that is typically served with a soft bread roll known as pav.

name: Puri
dis: Puri is an unleavened, fried Indian bread made with water, finer or coarser wheat flour, and occasionally cumin seeds.

name: Rasgulla
dis: Rasgulla is a traditional sweet that is usually served at the end of a meal, like many other Indian milk-based desserts

name: Raita
dis: Raita is a popular Indian side dish or a condiment made by combining thick yogurt with different fruits, vegetables, and spices, so it can be either sweet or savory and spicy.

name: Saag paneer
dis: Indian saag paneer is a famous vegetable curry which incorporates diced paneer cheese doused in a creamy mixture of fresh leafy greens.

name: Barfi
dis: Even though its name originates from Persia, barfi is an original Indian dessert which resembles a fudge.

name: Shahi paneer
dis: Originating from India's Moghul cuisine, shahi paneer is a cheese curry that is prepared with paneer cheese, onions, almond paste, and a rich, spicy tomato-cream sauce.

name: Dal tadka
dis: Dal tadka or tadkewali dal is a traditional lentil-based dish originating from the northern parts of India.

name: Rogan josh
dis: Rogan josh is an aromatic lamb curry that is believed to be of Persian origin, although today it is more closely associated with the Kashmir region of India.

name: Risotto
dis: This widely popular and extremely versatile group of dishes consists of a base of rice and stock.

name: Tagliatelle al ragù alla Bolognese

name: Pasta carbonara

name: Gnocchi
dis: This is the traditional Italian form of dumplings.

name: Ravioli

name: Tiramisù

name: Bruschetta
dis: Bruschetta is a traditional Italian appetizer that's nowadays popular throughout the world.

name: Pizza Margherita

name: Panna cotta

name: Carpaccio

name: Focaccia

name: Minestrone

name: Crostini

name: Parmigiana

name: Calzone Pizza

name: Spaghetti alle vongole

name: Pizza marinara

name: Frittata

name: Caprese Salad
dis: Nothing embodies the essence of summer in southern Italy like vibrant colors of the flavorful insalata Caprese, a true classic of Neapolitan cuisine.

name: Pizza capricciosa
dis: The name of this pizza literally translates to capricious, and seems quite appropriate, considering that the toppings tend to vary from one region to another.

name: Ciabatta
dis: Literally translated to a slipper, as a reference to its shape, ciabatta is an Italian type of white bread made with yeast and wheat flour.

name: Porchetta

name: Pizza quattro formaggi

name: Pizza ai funghi

name: Meunière

name: Magret de canard
dis: This dish of flash-seared duck breast dates back to the late 1950s, when French chef André Daguin first prepared a magret like a steak and served it medium-rare.

name: Mille feuilles
dis: Creamy, flaky, and delicate, this French dessert can be literally translated as a thousand leaves.

name: Pad Thai

name: Thai Curry

name: Tom yum

name: Green Curry

name: Yellow Curry
dis: One of three major curry types in Thailand is the famous yellow curry. Similar to its red and green counterparts

name: Red Curry
dis: Red curry is one of the most common curry varieties in Thailand. It combines red curry paste, coconut milk, vegetables and meat into a delectable and hearty meal.

name: Som tam
dis: Som tam is a green papaya salad mostly associated with the northeastern part of Thailand (Isaan), though it is often suggested that it first appeared in Laos.

name: Tom kha gai
dis: Tom kha gai is Thailand's delicious national dish coming from the north and bearing the influence of neighbouring Laos.

name: Massaman Curry
dis: Out of all Thai curry varieties, massaman curry stands out as the mildest, sweetest, and the most unusual type. It is a combination of creamy coconut milk, meat, potatoes, and a curry paste

name: Khao soi
dis: A signature dish of Northern Thailand, khao soi is a delicious coconut soup in which numerous regional influences were combined to create a truly spectacular dish.

name: Thai Grilled Chicken
dis: Thai grilled chicken is a poultry dish made by grilling or barbecuing a whole, marinated chicken.

name: Ruam mit
dis: Ruam mit is a popular Thai dessert made with ingredients such as coconut milk, sugar, tapioca pearls, corn, lotus root, sweet potatoes, beans, and jackfruit.

name: Khao lam
dis: Khao lam or kralan is a unique Thai dessert consisting of sweet sticky rice, either white or red, steamed in bamboo tubes.

name: Khao phat
dis: Khao phat is a simple Thai dish of stir-fried rice with vegetables that is traditionally prepared with jasmine rice, unlike the Chinese version which calls for plain white rice.

name: Phat kaphrao

name: Khao mok gai

name: Yen ta fo

name: Khao tom

name: Larb

name: Khao kha mu
dis: Khao kha mu is a Thai dish which consists of braised pork leg served over rice, complemented with a variety of side dishes and flavorful condiments.

name: Phat si-io

name: Suki
dis: Suki is the Thai version of a communal hot pot dish. It grew out of Chinese and Japanese traditions of preparing and cooking ingredients tableside in a shared bowl.

name: Roti canai

name: Mu wan

name: Khanom khrok

name: Pla thot

name: Jungle Curry

name: Khanom chin nam ya

name: Mu kratha

name: Chim chum

name: Kuai-tiao ruea
dis: Roughly translated as boat noodle soup, this Thai dish was initially sold from boats that navigated through Bangkok canals.

name: Khanom chan
